article.headline: Sacred Heart 86, Fairleigh Dickinson 82
article.story: HACKENSACK, N.J. (AP) -- Drew Shubik scored 19 points and three other Sacred Heart players scored in double figures as Sacred Heart defeated Fairleigh Dickinson 86-82 Tuesday night. Brice Brooks added 18 points for the Pioneers, Jarrid Frye 17 and Ryan Litke 14 as the Pioneers improved to 14-13 (10-6 Northeast Conference). FDU's Cameron Tyler led all scorers with 24 points. Andre Harris had 22, Michael Peeples 20 and Manny Ubilla 14 for the Knights (14-13, 9-7). A layup by Harris gave the Knights 39-38 lead with four minutes left in the first half, but the Pioneers outscored FDU 9-4 to take a 47-43 halftime lead. Sacred Heart shot 64 percent for the half. Sacred Heart surged to a 10-point lead in the second half, but FDU went on a 10-point run to knot the score at 71-71 with just under five minutes to play. A pair of free throws by Shubik with 4:04 to play gave Sacred Heart the lead for good at 75-74, and the Pioneers converted six free throws in the last two minutes to seal the game.
